verbose_text: At birth and 48 hr later, the newborns ' with PA had significantly higher levels of MDA in the cord blood, mean urinary uric acid / creatinine (UUA : Cr), protein / creatinine (UP : Cr), and MDA / creatinine ratio (UMDA : Cr) than the controls; their PA levels were correlated with the degree of hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy (HIE).
